commit.message: Release v2024
package separator for perl 5.38
e.g.

make clean removes manual.pdf

remove changebar package from build process
https://bugs.debian.org/cgi-bin/bugreport.cgi?bug=1046413
Release v2023.2

DONT_INCLUDE now affects \usepackage but not \input

prevents surprises when users have a .tex file with a name such as float.tex
and it gets processed as an image.

Fixes #82

array inside align

When an array was the first command inside a cell of an amsmath
align environment, the image was produced with displaymath and
was too wide (as wide as the page).

https://tex.stackexchange.com/questions/670076/bad-alignment-of-beginarray-endarray-with-latex2html
iso_map - check that regexp matched

babel package main option

New code to handle package options of the form "key=value".
Support for a <package>_setup routine that is called after all options
are loaded.

Fixes #81

LaTeX2HTML implementation of LaTeX package hyphenat

In the latex package, these commands allow hyphenation within the
words on either side of the dot, colon, slash and hyphen.  This
LaTeX2HTML package doesn't do anything to make hyphenation happen
within words in HTML, but it does allow the dot, colon slash or
hyphen in the text to come through.

There are still some commands from hyphenat.sty that are not
implemented here.

Fixes #80
Release v2023

update for latest pdftocairo

no longer includes "pt" in width and height attributes of svg
Release v2022.2

spacing of eqnarray and align

leftmost and rightmost columns expand to fill available space,
so that the main group of columns is centered.
one of the two contains the equation numbers.

spacing of eqnarry and align

specify width 50% in left and right columns, to fill available space.
prevents extra space around center column of eqnarray.
prevents column width proportional to size of each eqn.

commit.message:
revert PreviewBorder to 0.5bp

support download attribute for <A> tag

remove meta tags for distribution, etc

fix pnmcrop duplicated -sides option (aka PNMCROPOPT)

If the variable PNMCROPOPT is defined as "-sides" via config/config.pl
in pstoimg.bin, calling `pnmcrop -bot -sides $PNMCROPOPT` will give an
error, due to the duplicated option.
